Justin Williams is quite possibly the most networked man I have met in my entire life. If you aren't one to make connections and shy away from networking, do yourself a huge favor and muster enough energy to connect with Justin. He will be the first person to make introductions to the people you need to speak with.Aside from that, Justin is an incredibly intuitive entrepreneur. He has advised my company for just over a year now, and has helped us get out of some very deep water. He has deep insight into the elements of business that drive success at multiple levels and will guide you when you don't know what to do. One of the most valuable pieces of information that Justin gave us, was to speak with our super-users and start asking them WHY they love our products so much. This helped us better understand why others didn't and help reshape the path of our business.Justin is a lifeguard. He hands out lifelines when you are struggling with optimism and opportunism. You'd be wise to have him on your team.

December 19, 2013, Garrett reported directly to Justin

Justin is a driving force.  He "owns" his work, drives for and gets results.  I personally worked with him at the Arizona Technology Council while he was Director of the Southern Arizona Region.  He shepherded organizations through change (ITASA and SAIAA turning into AMIT, and then AMIT into the AZ Tech Council), took on new challenges, grew membership base, developed a critical mass, and breathed life into the operation that otherwise likely would have fizzled away and died without him.  He is intelligent, extremely well informed not just about the high-tech sectors of Southern Arizona, but about entrepreneurship in general and entrepreneurship within the high-tech sectors.  Justin is loyal, having stepped in as Interim Director when he was sorely needed to come back.  He is excellent in his relationship building skills, he is organized and highly-reliable.  I am happy to consider him my friend and I recommend him to anyone that is looking to partner or work with a self-starting, "A" player.
